other_tests.findings: Sinus rhythm with potential right ventricular hypertrophy and incomplete right bundle-branch block, suggestive of right ventricular volume overload.
Subcutaneous granuloma annulare with secondary metaplastic synovial pseudocyst. Histologic examination revealed necrobiotic collagen surrounded by a chronic inflammatory infiltrate.
other_tests.changes_over_time: One year after the initial diagnosis, the patient had a persistent lesion on the left shin, while other lesions appeared and disappeared at various locations. All nodules resolved two years after onset.
